[src:splay-tree/splay-tree] In order to reduce the number of restructuring operations, it is possible to replace the splaying with *semi-splaying*, in which an element is splayed only halfway towards the root.
[src:splay-tree/splay-tree] Another way to reduce restructuring is to do full splaying, but only in some of the access operations – only when the access path is longer than a threshold, or only in the first *m* access operations.
[src:splay-tree/splay-tree] The CBTree augments the splay tree with access counts at each node and uses them to restructure infrequently.
[src:splay-tree/splay-tree] A variant of the CBTree called the LazyCBTree does at most one rotation on each lookup.
[src:splay-tree/splay-tree] This is used along with an optimistic hand-over-hand validation scheme to make a concurrent self-adjusting tree.
